{"type":"message","id":"be5fa84e","parentId":"1ac97da1","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:51:04.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Developing Test Suite**\n\nI'm currently focused on the testing framework. Specifically, I'm setting up `tests/test_hft.py`. The goal here is to get all the pieces in place so that running `pytest` will yield positive results. I anticipate a comprehensive test suite to follow.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771167064523_335","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import pytest\nimport sys\nimport os\n\nsys.path.append(os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '..')))\n\nfrom src.utils.json_utils import dumps, loads\nimport orjson\n\ndef test_orjson_enforcement():\n    \"\"\"Ensure we are actually using orjson.\"\"\"\n    data = {\"test\": 123}\n    # Verify dumps returns string (decoded bytes)\n    assert isinstance(dumps(data), str)\n    # Verify basic functionality\n    assert loads(dumps(data)) == data\n\ndef test_speed_check():\n    \"\"\"Basic sanity check that it's fast enough (stub).\"\"\"\n    import time\n    data = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n    start = time.time()\n    for _ in range(1000):\n        loads(dumps(data))\n    end = time.time()\n    # 1000 ops should be instantaneous\n    assert (end - start) < 0.1\n","file_path":"tests/test_hft.py"},"thoughtSignature":"CiUBjz1rX4BzfgsMpepRl8cwJ9P8uqHJO60UrZohN4Ex7mk/g7mvCkoBjz1rX1lHt+TDpNmiNxE/lIN92l71zuP/cP0aHuFG21BRAheVe4cXAv7MYgdJYQkmQBGHJck02Qey4h5sU2aGP7Jwq2RYzSxnTQorAY89a1++wTmql93oxoH8/utbFYN2/SYYdBPlmPgjx8VTTrvZD3F75NggCQ=="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12815,"output":265,"cacheRead":11983,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13080,"cost":{"input":0.02563,"output":0.00318,"cacheRead":0.0023966,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.031206599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771167058340}}
