{"type":"message","id":"341810d8","parentId":"a9c0f882","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:51:10.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Testing the Integration**\n\nMy latest thought is to create `tests/integration_sandbox.py`. This script will function as an integration test, ensuring the system logic functions correctly. Initially, I plan to verify imports and instantiation of core classes within the `agent_wrapper.py` module, to make sure everything's set up correctly.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771167070568_336","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import sys\nimport os\nimport logging\nimport asyncio\n\n# Setup paths\nsys.path.append(os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '..')))\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"IntegrationSandbox\")\n\nasync def test_integration():\n    logger.info(\"Starting Integration Sandbox Test...\")\n    \n    # 1. Test Imports\n    try:\n        from src.utils.json_utils import dumps, loads\n        from src.main import main\n        logger.info(\"Imports passed.\")\n    except ImportError as e:\n        logger.error(f\"Import failed: {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    # 2. Test JSON Utils (Critical HFT component)\n    data = {\"e\": \"trade\", \"p\": 100}\n    serialized = dumps(data)\n    deserialized = loads(serialized)\n    if data != deserialized:\n        logger.error(\"JSON Utils Integrity Check Failed\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    logger.info(\"JSON Utils Check passed.\")\n\n    # 3. Test File Structure\n    required_dirs = [\"logs\", \"src\", \"tests\"]\n    for d in required_dirs:\n        if not os.path.exists(d):\n             logger.error(f\"Missing directory: {d}\")\n             sys.exit(1)\n    logger.info(\"File structure passed.\")\n    \n    logger.info(\"Integration Sandbox Test: SUCCESS\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    asyncio.run(test_integration())\n","file_path":"tests/integration_s